    details: "pg ?, col ?",
    sourceDate: "1870-05-05",
    summary: "Tom Allen's belt presentation at Theatre Comique was postponed due to safety issues and a missing sparring partner, with rescheduling after his fight with Jem Mace.",
    link: "http://statehistoricalsocietyofmissouri.org/cdm/ref/collection/dmr3/id/2383",
    localCopyEdited: "images/articles/image-034.jpg",
    localCopyFull: "images/articles/image-034b.jpg",
    id: "034",
    text: "The presentation of a splendid belt to Tom Allen was to have taken place last night at the Theatre Comique, but was postponed a second time. Several circumstances combined to render a postponement desirable. The condition of the road in front of the theatre, owing to the caving in of the sewer, was such that a casualty might have resulted from a large number of people passing over it—the hall was imperfectly lighted with gasoline, and Coburn, who was to have sparred with Allen, was out of town. It is intended to make the presentation after the combat between Allen and Mace, on the 10th instant."
