    id: "097",
    text: "The proposed prize fight between John I. Sullivan, of this city, and Tom Allen, who has just returned from England, for $5,000 and the championship of the world, is creating great excitement here. Tom Allen's backer arrived here today ready to match Allen, and Sullivan will be here in a few days, when Kilbride, his backer, will cover the $1,000. Richard K. Fox has posted with Hill, and the representative will meet Allen in New York on November 10 to arrange the match. Allen, with his backer, will leave for New York tomorrow. Sullivan has notified Kilbride to accept the challenge issued on behalf of Allen, to fight in three months within one hundred miles of Kansas City.",
    summary: "John L. Sullivan is set to fight England-returned Tom Allen for a $5,000 purse and world championship, highlighting 19th-century boxing's fierce rivalries and honor."
