    id: "099",
    text: "New York, December 6.—Up to 10 o'clock last evening neither W. E. Harding, for Tom Allen, nor Bob Farrell, for Sullivan, had appeared at Harry Hill's. Mr. Hill said he would return to Mr. Fox his check for $1,000 which he had posted as a forfeit for Tom Allen, and wash his hands of the whole affair, especially as Allen said yesterday: “I have not been out of the house since the exhibition. I have been sick. I am going to Chicago to see a glove contest between Sullivan and Elliott, and if I mend a bit I will have a go with the winner. There is another good night left in me yet.”",
    summary: "Tom Allen's illness led to the cancellation of his fight with Sullivan. Promoter Harry Hill refunded the forfeit, while Allen eyed a future bout with Sullivan-Elliott's winner."
